            <p:rationale>The reuse of IT systems that are already available is often the simplest and cheapest solution. Reused Custom Development is often very expensive, especially when you factor in the cost of maintenance over time. Buying standard IT solutions is cheaper than custom development, as long as they are not customized, and maintenance is performed by the supplier. Knowledge of common standard IT solutions is widely available in the market.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>The first step is to check whether existing IT systems are in place for certain functionality. If no suitable standard applications are available in the market, then one should proceed to customization. Custom Development is avoided as much as possible; Standard Applications are defined as many out-of-the-box components as one can use.</p:implications>
